This paper deals with the training of classifiers with data-dependent constraints, which is a problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses fairness metrics, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of constraints to achieve policy goals, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also discusses the generalization performance of classifiers, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
